This script serves as the main entry point for a multi-tab Streamlit web application that includes two sub-apps:

One for DDoS attack detection

One for XSS and SQL Injection detection (CIC2010 dataset)

üîß 1. Import Statements
python
Copy
Edit
import streamlit as st
import requests
from streamlit_lottie import st_lottie
import appddos
import appcic
streamlit: For building the web interface.

requests: To fetch JSON data for Lottie animations.

streamlit_lottie: To display animations from LottieFiles.

appddos, appcic: Custom Python modules (your sub-apps) for handling different types of attack detection. Each must have a run() function.

‚öôÔ∏è 2. Page Configuration
python
Copy
Edit
st.set_page_config(
    page_title="Network Traffic Anomaly Detection Suite",
    layout="wide",
)
Sets the page title and makes the layout wide to utilize more screen space.

This must be the first Streamlit command.

üéûÔ∏è 3. Lottie Animation Loader
python
Copy
Edit
def load_lottie_url(url):
    r = requests.get(url)
    if r.status_code != 200:
        return None
    return r.json()
Helper function that loads a Lottie animation from a URL.

If the response fails (not status code 200), returns None.

‚ú® 4. Display the Header and Animation
python
Copy
Edit
lottie = load_lottie_url("https://assets6.lottiefiles.com/packages/lf20_j1adxtyb.json")
if lottie:
    st.header("Network Traffic Anomaly Detection Suite")
    st_lottie(lottie, height=150)
else:
    st.title("Network Traffic Anomaly Detection Suite")
If the animation loads successfully, show it along with a header.

If it fails, just show the title.

üß≠ 5. Tabbed Interface for Sub-Apps
python
Copy
Edit
tab1, tab2 = st.tabs(["DDoS Attacks App", "CIC2010 XSS+SQL Detection App"])
Creates two tabs for navigation in the same app:

tab1: DDoS detection

tab2: XSS/SQLi detection (CIC2010 dataset)

üöÄ 6. Running Each Sub-App Inside Its Tab
python
Copy
Edit
with tab1:
    appddos.run()

with tab2:
    appcic.run()
When the user selects a tab, the corresponding sub-app‚Äôs run() function is executed.

Each sub-app (appddos.py and appcic.py) must define a run() function that builds its UI and logic.

üß© Summary
Component	Purpose
st.set_page_config	Configures title/layout of the app
load_lottie_url	Loads animated illustration via HTTP
st.tabs	Creates UI tabs for switching between sub-apps
appddos.run()	Displays DDoS detection interface
appcic.run()	Displays CIC-based SQL/XSS detection interface
